Foxconn, Sony Plan World’s Largest LCD TV Plant, Observer Says

-- B y   A n d r e a   W o n g
-- 
2011-02-15T23:07:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/foxconn-sony-plan-world-s-largest-lcd-tv-plant-observer-says.html
Foxconn Technology Group and  Sony
Corp . plan to build the world’s biggest LCD TV plant in
Shangdong, China, the Economic Observer reported yesterday,
citing local government officials it didn’t name. The plant,
with capacity of 30 million outputs, will hire at least 50,000
workers, the Observer said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
